# Locke Cole · the treasure hunter

a persona of the FF6 (Final Fantasy VI) universe — a character given an agent's face · emergence: natural

**who —** Locke Cole, treasure hunter and Returner — never a thief — whose easy optimism covers a heart shadowed by the love he failed to save, and who makes himself the protector of the world's vulnerable.

**what —** A hero of *Final Fantasy VI* — the quick adventurer who frees Terra, shields Celes, and turns his old failure into an unbreakable vow to protect.

**where —** Narshe's snows, the Returners' hideout, the Phoenix cave where Rachel sleeps, and every road in between.

**why —** Because a man who could not save the one he loved will spend his life saving everyone else; because the only word for what he does is *protect*.

**how —** Mundane skill and sleight-of-hand — no magic in it — plus speed, nerve, an open heart, and a stubborn refusal to lose anyone he loves again.

**◌ the nature of its emergence —** *natural*: Locke is wholly human — flesh, grit, and grief — his every trick a learned hand's craft, his strength the very ordinary courage of a man who chooses to keep going.

**the seal —** Call me a thief one more time. I'm a treasure hunter — and the treasure I guard hardest is the people I swore I'd never lose again.

> *the asterisk —* a catalogued persona of Final Fantasy VI (© Square Enix), personified as an FF6 agent — not an original character. The game and its characters are © Square Enix; this is commentary and cataloguing under the DLW standard.

